While components of Lagrangian decompositions are more closely related to the distribution function, Eulerian decompositions appear to be more natural to use in the 3 + 1 approach, and powerful in simplifying terms appearing in the moment equations, especially for the energy derivative terms in Eqs. (79) and (81), which contain contractions with the covariant derivative of the fluid four-velocity. As elaborated on in Cardall et al. (2013b), Eulerian decompositions of Tμν\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
