				\begin{document}$$\big ({\mathscr {W}}_{j}^{\nu \rho }-Wv_{j}{\mathscr {S}}^{\nu \rho }\big )$$\end{document}, contracted with the covariant derivative of the fluid four-velocity, and can be written in a form similar to Eq. (112).

The Lagrangian two-moment model presented here [Eqs. (116) and (118)] is the basis for several codes used to model neutrino transport in core-collapse supernovae: Müller et al. (2010) used it in conjunction with the conformal flatness approximation to GR (CFA) and ray-by-ray neutrino transport transport; and Just et al. (2015) and Skinner et al. (2019) used this model in its O(v/c)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\mathscr {O}}(v/c)$$\end{document} limit to develop multi-dimensional neutrino transport codes.

