Kershaw closure A different approach to the closure problem was proposed by Kershaw (1976). The key idea behind the Kershaw closure is to consider the bounds on the moments generated by the underlying distribution function. For a nonnegative distribution function (f≥0\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
