				\begin{document}$$\sim 10\,\hbox {km}$$\end{document} in the core, pair production from bremsstrahlung dominates. On the other hand, between the heavy-flavor thermalization surfaces and the shock, production by electron–positron pair annihilation is consistently largerFig. 7
